<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="27" type="chorology">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Chorology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Puthz" authorityYear="1983" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Stenus pieperi" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pieperi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">Stenus pieperi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from Alamdeh, West Mazandaran (
<bibRefCitation author="Puthz, V" journalOrPublisher="Senckenbergiana biologica" pageId="19" pageNumber="36" pagination="347 - 362" refId="B57" refString="Puthz, V, 1983. Einige Stenus -Arten aus dem Kaukasus und Elburs (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). 190. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Steninen. Senckenbergiana biologica 63: 347 - 362" title="Einige Stenus - Arten aus dem Kaukasus und Elburs (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae). 190. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Steninen." volume="63" year="1983">Puthz 1983</bibRefCitation>
: 353). Our recent records further east, which are the first after the description, indicate that the species is endemic to the Hyrcanian forest zone of the Elburz Mountains from about 50°30'E eastwards to about 53°10'E (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–24" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 19 - 24. Distribution of Steninae in Iran. 19. Stenus mendicus species group: △ Stenus alienigenus, ○ Stenus ignotus, ● Stenus orientis; 20. Stenus ochropus - ludyi - coarcticollis species group: □ Stenus barbarae, ▲ Stenus confrater, ▲ Stenus darius, ● Stenus derwisch, △ Stenus guilanensis, ■ Stenus kambyses, ● Stenus martensi, ○ Stenus ochropus, ■ Stenus pieperi, ➕ Stenus ressli, ➕ Stenus wittmeri; 21. Stenus pallitarsis species group: ● Stenus arabicus, △ Stenus butrintensis, ○ Stenus claritarsis; 22. Stenus picipes species group: ○ Stenus ganglbaueri, ● Stenus picipes; 23. Stenus pusillus species group: □ Stenus lenkoranus, ● Stenus machulkai, ● Stenus viti; 24. Stenus similis species group: △ Stenus bernhauerianus, ■ Stenus cicindeloides, ○ Stenus similis." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.63.5885.figures19-24" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/74431" pageId="10" pageNumber="27">20</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
